metatags.og:description:
Google Certified Business Intelligence & Data Analyst | Python, SQL, R, Tableau, Power BI, Excel | Mathematician & Researcher · Numbers have always been my thing. I even earned a distinction in my Master's degree in Mathematics (with honors!). During my academic journey, I published two research papers in international journals, showcasing my ability to draw meaningful conclusions. As a result, I have over 2 years of experience as a Mathematics Tutor and 3 years of research experience. This journey taught me how to break down complex problems and explain them in a clear, concise way.

But numbers alone weren’t enough - I craved the challenge of using them to understand how the world works. I see patterns everywhere. I love analyzing systems, asking “why” and getting deep into what most people overlook. That passion led me to earn Google’s Professional Certificates in Data Analytics and Business Intelligence, and I’ve been building ever since.
